    <dashboard name='UCUCI Bank Loan Portfolio Health &amp; Repayment Performance Analysis' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='1'>UCUCI Bank Loan Portfolio Health &amp; Repayment Performance Analysis</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-description'>
          <format attr='border-width' value='2' />
          <format attr='background-color' value='#00000000' />
          <format attr='text-align' value='center' />
          <format attr='font-weight' value='bold' />
          <format attr='text-align' id='story-description_9' value='left' />
          <format attr='text-orientation' id='story-description_9' value='0' />
          <format attr='background-color' id='story-description_9' value='#ddebf0' />
          <format attr='border-width' id='story-description_9' value='1' />
          <format attr='border-style' id='story-description_9' value='solid' />
        </style-rule>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='1247' />
          <format attr='color' value='#1b1b1b' />
          <format attr='font-size' value='10' />
          <format attr='background-color' value='#d4d4d4' />
          <format attr='font-weight' value='bold' />
          <format attr='font-style' value='normal' />
          <format attr='text-decoration' value='none' />
        </style-rule>
        <style-rule element='story-title'>
          <format attr='background-color' value='#efebe8' />
          <format attr='border-width' value='2' />
          <format attr='border-style' value='solid' />
          <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98120' id='7' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='99044' x='478' y='940'>
            <zone h='5758' id='8' type-v2='title' w='99044' x='478' y='940'>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone h='92362' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='99044' x='478' y='6698'>
              <zone fixed-size='183' h='21504' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='99044' x='478' y='6698' />
              <zone h='70858' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='99044' x='478' y='28202'>
                <flipboard active-id='2' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                  <story-points>
                    <story-point caption='Portfolio Health Snapshot:&#10;This dashboard gives leadership a high-level view of how much was funded, how much has been repaid, and how much of the portfolio is current, fully paid, delinquent, or charged off.&#10;&#10;The overall LRR and default rate provide the first view of whether the loan portfolio is healthy or under repayment pressure.' captured-sheet='Executive Portfolio Health' id='2' />
                    <story-point caption='Risk Grades Reveal Repayment Differences:&#10;Loan grade is a major risk indicator assigned at origination. Comparing LRR, default rate, and interest rate by grade helps evaluate whether safer grades repay better and whether riskier grades are priced appropriately.&#10;&#10;If lower grades show weaker repayment and higher default, they should receive stricter underwriting, exposure limits, or adjusted pricing.' captured-sheet='Dashboard 4' id='3' />
                    <story-point caption='Debt Burden and Income Affect Repayment Capacity:&#10;Borrower repayment capacity is influenced by income, debt-to-income ratio, and monthly installment burden. These factors help identify borrowers who may struggle to repay even before default occurs.&#10;&#10;High DTI and high installment burden segments should be monitored closely and may require smaller approved loan amounts or shorter repayment terms.&#10;' captured-sheet='Risk &amp; Repayment Drivers' id='6' />
                    <story-point caption='Loan Purpose Shows Where Exposure and Risk Concentrate:&#10;Loan purpose helps identify why borrowers take loans and which purposes contribute most to funded exposure and charged-off exposure.&#10;&#10;Large exposure purposes are important, but the highest-risk purposes are those combining high funded amount with high default or charged-off exposure.' captured-sheet='Dashboard 5' id='7' />
                    <story-point caption='Key Risk Factors Linked to Repayment and Default :&#10;Correlation analysis helps identify which numeric factors are most associated with repayment performance and default risk. This supports deeper investigation of interest rate, DTI, income, installment burden, and revolving utilization.&#10;&#10;Factors negatively associated with LRR or positively associated with default risk should become part of monitoring and underwriting rules.' captured-sheet='Dashboard 6' id='8' />
                    <story-point caption='Is Risk Being Priced Correctly?&#10;Risk-based pricing should charge higher interest rates to riskier borrowers. Comparing default rate, LRR, and average interest rate by grade and sub-grade helps identify whether pricing is aligned with actual repayment outcomes.&#10;&#10;Sub-grades with high default rates and weak LRR should be reviewed for repricing, tighter approval rules, or reduced exposure.' captured-sheet='Pricing, Recovery &amp; Loss Exposure' id='9' />
                    <story-point caption='Recovery Strategy Can Reduce Final Credit Losses :&#10;Charged-off loans reduce portfolio health, but recoveries can reduce final credit losses. Recovery analysis helps identify where collections teams should prioritize efforts.&#10;&#10;Recovery strategies should focus on charged-off segments with large exposure and meaningful recovery opportunity.' captured-sheet='Dashboard 7' id='10' />
                    <story-point caption='Recommended Actions to Improve LRR and Final Conclusion :&#10;Here are some recommended actions mentioned so that the objective of improving the LRR is achieved.' captured-sheet='' id='11' />
                  </story-points>
                </flipboard>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='62280' hidden='true' id='9' story-point-id='11' type-v2='text' w='95896' x='2112' y='29142'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>1. Tighten credit approval for high-risk grades, high DTI bands, and risky loan purposes.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>2. Recalibrate grade and sub-grade pricing where default risk is not adequately compensated.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>3. Monitor delinquent and high-burden borrowers earlier to prevent charge-off.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>4. Align funded amount and term with borrower repayment capacity.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>5. Prioritize recovery strategies for charged-off segments with large exposure.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>6. Grow healthier segments with strong LRR, low default rate, and stable borrower profiles.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>7. Build a recurring portfolio dashboard for leadership review.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>Improving LRR requires coordinated action across underwriting, pricing, monitoring, collections, and growth strategy.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>The analysis shows that Loan Repayment Rate can be improved by identifying weak repayment segments, controlling high-default borrower profiles, aligning pricing with risk, and improving recovery focus. Grade, sub-grade, DTI, income, purpose, interest rate, and loan status are key decision variables for improving portfolio health.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontname='Tableau Medium'>UCUCI Bank should use these insights to strengthen lending decisions, reduce default exposure, and grow the loan portfolio sustainably.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{645BA76A-FC6C-4BC5-A6CF-54AE744E758C}' />
    </dashboard>
  </dashboards>
